<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-20T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1/133: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Tittmann</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-20T13:00:00-05:00">January
                                    20, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6. Your No. 6, January 18, 5 p.m. The Department entirely approves your
                            efforts to discourage the League Secretariat with regard to the
                            advisability of your presence at The Hague at the time of the meetings
                            of the Organizing Committee. We do not feel that it is <pb facs="0319" n="310" xml:id="pg_310"/> either desirable or necessary that anyone
                            from the Consulate proceed to The Hague for this purpose.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>